	21 - Sequence err while performing WRITE
	22 - Primary duplicate key found
	23 - Record not found or File not found
	24 - Key outside boundary of file
	35 - File not opened
	92 - Opening a opened file
	98 - File is locked - Open failed

- What do you mean by abends in JCL? Write different JCL abend codes.
	When a programme ends abnormally during a step, it is called an abend. 
		S0C1: Missing or misspelled DD name / Called subprogram not found
		S0C4: Read/Write to unopened file
		S0C5: Closing unopened file
		S0C7: Is caused by bad data / Numeric operation performed on alphabetic field
		S222: When an operator cancels a job because the programme seeks a resource that is unavailable, this error occurs.
		S322: The time allotted to a job, job step, or procedure has exceeded the limit, resulting in a Timeout error.
		S237: When the volume's end is reached, this error occurs.
		Space Issue:
			SB37: max. 16 extents are currently allocated 
			SD37: the secondary allocation has not been specified
			SE37: End of volume with no further volume specified
		S806: Load module not foung in JOBLIB/STEPLIB

