Now we need to add a restart logic in case of failure based on below condition:
1. use checkpoint value to store the last committed record on DB with the commit frequency as 10 . This will be an insert to restart table.
2. For every next commit it will be an update on the restart table with the new checkpoint
3. Use customer id to read the data from the checkpoint tables to baseline the next restart
4. Read the file and ignore the records till the checkpoint id and start process after that
5. Use commit at the end of the program just to make sure all the records are committed after the last commit.
6. Post completion of the normal job/failed  job remove the entry from restart table for the entry made of that instance